      <h2>Data Collection and Usage</h2>
      <p>
        By using the TiMA app (referred to as "the app"), users acknowledge and agree that personal data — including but not limited to first name, last name, email address, and the last three months of app data (which includes but is not limited to planned, scheduled, and reviewed items) — may be collected and securely stored in the app’s database.
      </p>
      <p>
        This data is required to enable the core functionalities of the app and to provide a smooth and personalized user experience. After this period, the app data will be automatically deleted.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Data Protection</h2>
      <p>
        All personal data is handled with a high level of security. Information is stored using standard encryption methods and protected by appropriate access control measures. Technical and organizational safeguards are implemented to prevent unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction of user data.
      </p>
    </section>

